      <body>
			<div type="edition">
				<ab>
					<lb n="1"/>
					<g type="siddham"/>
					<g type="ddanda">.</g> tdaṃḥ ḅaṁḥ O lu
					snuḥ
					<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied>ihavikrama ḅaṁḥ sniḥ hraṁ su rla hniṁ tiṁ phvuṃ plaṁ ta kiṁ kha O sniḥ sniḥ plaṁ
					su plaṁ rla
					tko tiṁ phvuṃ
					npu tiṁ tdaṃḥ ḅaṁḥ O ru kleḥ yaṁ </ab>
				<!-- MM2AG: should I do anything with the red in the RTF? -->
				<!-- AG2MM3: editing conventions to be revised. -->
			</div>
			<div type="apparatus">
				<listApp>
					<app loc="1">
						<lem>lu</lem>
						<note>See note on PYU <ref target="DHARMA_INSPYU00001">1</ref>.</note>
						<note>Blagden also proposed &lt;roṃ&gt;, &lt;reṃ&gt; and &lt;nūṃ&gt; as possible readings.</note>
					</app>
					<app loc="1">
						<lem>npu</lem>
						<note>See note on PYU <ref target="DHARMA_INSPYU00005">5</ref>.</note>
					</app>
				<app loc="1">
						<lem>lu</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">(bhūṃ)</rdg>
						<rdg source="bib:ThaMyat1963_01">bhū</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>snuḥ</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">s(n)ūḥ</rdg>
						<rdg source="bib:ThaMyat1963_01">snūḥ</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>su rla</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">sū (de)</rdg>
						<rdg source="bib:ThaMyat1963_01">sū (de)</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>plaṁ</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">p(ḷ)aṁ</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>kiṁ kha</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">(k)iṁ (kha)</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>plaṁ</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">p(ḷ)aṁ</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>su plaṁ rla</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">sū p(ḷ)aṁ (de)</rdg>
						<rdg source="bib:ThaMyat1963_01">sū plaṁ (de)</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>tko</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">t(k)o</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>phvuṃ</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:ThaMyat1963_01">phvu</rdg>
						<!-- MM: PR has phvuṃ earlier; I suspect the absence of ṃ here is accidental -->
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>npu</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">(t)pū</rdg>
						<rdg source="bib:ThaMyat1963_01">nsū</rdg>
					</app><app loc="1">
						<lem>kleḥ</lem>
						<rdg source="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01">(kḷ)eḥ</rdg>
					</app></listApp>
			</div>
			<div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
				<p>Blagden:</p>
				<ab>Year 80 (718 AD), 2nd month, 4th day; Sihavikrama died, aged 44 years, 9 months and 20 days.</ab>
				<p>San Win:</p>
				<ab>On the 20th day of the 9th month of the (Pyu = 363) year 44 King Siha Vikrama died. He was 80 years old.</ab>
			</div>
			<div type="commentary">
				<p>Vague traces of punctuation signs followed by another text after this one are visible on the estampages.</p>
				<p>Note the allograph of &lt;u&gt; in &lt;phvuṃ&gt;.</p>
				<p>Note &lt;sniḥ sniḥ plaṁ su plaṁ rla tko tiṁ phvuṃ nsu tiṁ&gt; ‘on year 44, month 9 (and?) day 20’</p>
			</div>
			<div type="bibliography">
				<!--ASI 1911-12, 147. — ASB 1912, 7, 11. — Blagden 1913-14 (B). — PR, 47 (B), 50. — PPPB I, 48, 57 n. 13, 126-7. — Shafer 1943: 339. — Guy 2014: 76-7 (cat. 24).-->
				<!--[Todo: markup citedRange elements if necessary]-->
				<p><bibl><ptr target="bib:ASI"/><citedRange>1911-12: 147</citedRange></bibl> notes the discovery of 006 along with 005, two urns “inscribed with legends in the Pyu character”. <bibl><ptr target="bib:ASB"/><citedRange>1912: 7, 11</citedRange></bibl>, also notes Venkayya’s reading of the name [S]ihavikrama. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Blagden1913-1914_01"/><citedRange>(B1)</citedRange></bibl> provides a complete transliteration and a tentative translation. (He also mentions the second, highly effaced inscription, his B2, that follows on the same line as B1, but he attempts no reading. This inscription is now generally regarded as unrecoverable.) <bibl><ptr target="bib:ThaMyat1963_01"/><citedRange>47 (D), 50</citedRange></bibl>, has eye copy, a Burmese transliteration (with minor changes from Blagden) and English translation. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Luce1985_01"/><citedRange>I, 48, 57 n. 13, 126-7</citedRange></bibl>, is an overview. <bibl><ptr target="bib:SeinWin2016_01"/><citedRange>63</citedRange></bibl> has a transliteration in Burmese script (again, with minor changes) and a glossary. Re-edited here from published photographs.</p>
				<listBibl type="primary"><bibl><ptr target="bib:CPI2018_01"/><citedRange unit="item">DHARMA_INSPYU00006</citedRange></bibl></listBibl><listBibl type="secondary">
